Ad Text:
Are you wanting to work for an organisation that values their people, invests in communities and has a commitment to our environment? Do you share a passion for maintaining a continual focus on Making a Difference with Real Care to customers and employees? If this sounds like you, then we have your next opportunity.




About O’Brien® Glass 

O’Brien® Glass is one of Australia’s most trusted household brands, known for delivering exceptional service and quality for over 100 years. With a national footprint and a strong commitment to innovation, we’re modernising the way we use data to support smarter decision making across the business. When you join O’Brien®, you join a team driven by values, collaboration, and a genuine focus on helping our people succeed. 




About the Role 

We’re looking for an experienced Data Engineer to join our Business Intelligence team on an initial 12-month fixed term basis and help shape the future of data at O’Brien® Glass. 

In this role, you will design, build, and maintain reliable end-to-end data pipelines and models that support accurate, timely, and trusted insights across the organisation. 

Working closely with the Business Intelligence Manager, you’ll play a key role in improving data quality, automating core processes, and lifting our overall data capability. 




What You’ll Be Doing 

Building and maintaining automated data pipelines, transformations, and reporting solutions 

Ensuring data accuracy and reliability through rigorous testing and validation 

Analysing complex business and financial data to support decision-making 

Troubleshooting data issues and supporting continuous improvement initiatives 

Partnering with IT, BI, and business stakeholders, along with external consultants 




What You’ll Bring 

4–5 years’ experience in Data Engineering or BI 

Strong SQL, ETL/ELT, and data modelling expertise 

Excellent communication and documentation skills 

Strong business acumen and attention to detail 

Bachelor degree and/or relevant vendor certifications 

Nice to Have: 

Snowflake certification 

Experience with Finance, Supply Chain, Service Management, or Call Centre systems 

Exposure to Digital Unix 




Why You’ll Love Working at O’Brien® Glass 

Be part of an exciting transformation of our data environment 

Supportive and collaborative BI and IT teams 

Opportunities to influence data processes and deliver meaningful business value 

Work for a trusted Australian brand with strong values and a people-first culture 

 

Ready to make an impact? Apply now and help shape the future of data at O’Brien® Glass. 




If you meet the above criteria and you’re seeking a rewarding career with a nationally recognised household brand, then we would love to hear from you. Apply Now!




At O'Brien®, we put our customer at the heart of everything that we do, serving more than 360,000 Customers each year, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days a year. O'Brien is also part of Belron®, worldwide leader in vehicle glass repair, replacement and recalibration services, operating in 40 countries across 6 continents

Privacy: To review and consider your application, O'Brien® collects personal information. To understand what is collected and why, carefully review the Applicant Privacy Notice presented during your online application and/or review our Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.

Agencies: O'Brien® does not accept unsolicited resumes or outreach from recruiting agencies. Absent a signed agreement and approval from O'Brien® to submit candidates to a specific requisition, we will not approve payment to any third party.

Ad Text:
The Company

This organisation is a well-established, mid–large enterprise with a strong reputation for quality, governance and professionalism. The finance function is highly regarded internally and is led by an experienced, supportive leadership team that values collaboration, continuous improvement and high performance.

The culture is collegiate, delivery-focused and inclusive, with senior finance leaders who genuinely invest in process excellence and developing best practice across reporting and controls.

Offices are based in Melbourne's south east so ideal for anyone living locally who is comfortable working on site Monay - Friday.

The Position

This is a 9-month fixed-term contract commencing late January or early February, based 5 days on site in Melbourne’s south eastern suburbs.

Reporting to the Head of Finance, the Financial Reporting Manager will act as a senior technical lead responsible for the integrity of the general ledger and all local and parent company reporting. The role plays a critical part in month-end, quarter-end and year-end close and provides senior-level backup and overflow support during peak periods.

Key duties will involve:

Completion of accurate and timely financial reporting and optimisation of reporting and financial processes to increase accuracy, minimise internal control gaps and manage risk
Ensuring that daily accounting functions are performed accurately by local teams and that parent company reporting is completed within timeframe
Documentation of financial policies and procedures in line with internal audit requirements
Remediation of audit items within agreed timeframe
Responding to and resolve complex financial queries from internal finance team or various department leaders

In addition to core reporting responsibilities, this role offers genuine scope to:

Improve, streamline and automate reporting processes
Reduce manual intervention and control risk using Power Query / BI solutions
Contribute to ad hoc, project-based work across finance and the wider business
The environment is fast paced and will suit someone comfortable operating with autonomy, minimal hand-holding and competing deadlines.

Why Apply?
Immediate impact role with visibility at senior finance leadership level
Highly collaborative team with strong leadership and clear direction
Opportunity to drive process improvement and automation, not just “keep the lights on”
Exposure to complex reporting and governance requirements within a mature organisation
Well-structured finance function with strong controls and audit discipline
Ideal location for anyone seeking an opportunity in the south east
Chance to start quickly and secure a great role lasting for the bulk of 2026
The Successful Candidate Profile

You will be a senior accounting professional who thrives in hands-on, delivery-focused environments and is comfortable stepping into a leadership-capacity role from day one.

Key requirements include:

CA or CPA qualification with 10+ years’ experience in mid to large organisations
Strong management reporting experience
Demonstrated ability to lead through influence, provide senior-level backup and manage complex ad hoc requests
Proven process improvement mindset with a track record of automating or optimising reporting
Advanced experience with Power Query, Power BI or similar automated BI tools
Strong understanding of financial controls, audit requirements and risk management
Ability to operate at pace, prioritise effectively and meet tight deadlines
This role will suit someone who enjoys being “in the detail” while also thinking strategically about how finance can operate better, faster and with lower risk.

Bring a human‑centred lens to AI adoption and help shape how customers and employees experience emerging technology, while building your career in a growing innovation function.

About the Role

As an AI Adoption Specialist, you will support the successful adoption of AI by designing and validating customer and employee experiences across claims and customer service initiatives. Working closely with delivery squads, you will turn research insights into practical patterns that teams can apply as AI capabilities scale across the business.

What You’ll Do

Design, test and validate AI‑enabled solutions with customers and internal teams, adapting research methods to suit emerging and ambiguous use cases
Create conversational and other designs, workflows, wireframes and UI concepts that support clear, usable AI experiences
Partner with delivery squads to plan and run testing across design, UAT and post‑launch phases, aligning activity with sprint cycles
Translate insights into practical tools such as checklists, templates and design patterns that teams can use immediately
Support squads to build capability in user‑centred validation approaches for AI, sharing guidance and applied learning
Analyse insights from research, analytics and interaction data to identify patterns, opportunities and experience improvements

What You’ll Bring

Experience selecting and applying research and testing methodologies in complex or emerging problem spaces
Background in experience design, service design or behavioural research, with the ability to design and test digital solutions
Strong ability to synthesise qualitative and quantitative data and convert findings into clear, actionable outputs
Experience working in agile delivery environments alongside cross‑functional teams
Confidence communicating insights and recommendations to both technical and non‑technical audiences
Comfort working in forming teams and evolving domains, with a curious and adaptable approach

What You’ll Enjoy

Access our award‑winning Shine platform, your central hub for exclusive perks, wellbeing support, career development, and recognition

Hybrid working, flexible leave, 20 weeks paid parental leave, and up to 5 days paid flexible leave annually
Paid study support, career breaks, on‑the‑job learning, and a $1,000 referral bonus for eligible employees
Free wellbeing coaching, a dedicated Employee Council, and confidential EAP access
Discounts at 400+ retailers, insurance savings, gym memberships, and reduced super fees
Paid volunteer leave, donation matching, and unlimited emergency response leave
Performance‑based bonuses and Suncorp shares for eligible employees
Diversity is celebrated through employee resource groups and inclusive policies for all families

Explore our full benefits: www.suncorpgroup.com.au/careers/benefits

At Suncorp, we believe we are our best when our workforce reflects the diversity of the communities we serve. We provide reasonable adjustments in recruitment and the workplace; please let us know what you need.

About Us

At Sportsbet, we’re all about bringing excitement to life for our 2 million customers. As part of the global Flutter Group, we’re a tight-knit team of 1,300 in Melbourne, Sydney, and Darwin, passionate about challenging the status quo. We’re proud to be recognized as one of LinkedIn’s Top 25 Companies and one of the Top 10 Workplaces for Women.

We’re an inclusive employer who celebrates diversity and is committed to helping you thrive. Whether you’re looking for flexibility, career growth, or a supportive environment, we’re here to help you succeed.

Committed To Responsible Gambling

Our commitment to responsible gambling is genuine and demonstrated through the wide range of responsible gambling initiatives and tools.

We’re proud to be the leaders in responsible gambling in our industry, not just locally, but globally.

About the Role

As a Business Analyst within the Media & Content Value Stream, you’ll play a key role in shaping the future of our streaming, video and content experiences across Sportsbet’s platforms. Acting as a bridge between business stakeholders and technology teams, you’ll translate business needs into actionable solutions across a range of technologies including customer-facing web and mobile platforms, back-office systems and internal tools.

You’ll be responsible for eliciting, analysing and validating requirements to deliver high-quality solutions that meet business objectives. This role involves close collaboration with feature teams including UX designers, developers and testers as well as working independently or alongside other Business Analysts.

As a Business Analyst at Sportsbet, you will be working within a Feature Team and perform the following:

Be the interface between stakeholders across both business and technology including development and testing teams
Elicit and analyse requirements from stakeholders using a variety of techniques (e.g., workshops, interviews, data analysis)
Maintain a high level of requirements quality throughout the delivery lifecycle
Use data and processes during analysis to clarify and validate requirements
Expected to facilitate ceremonies like Backlog refinement, Sprint planning, etc

 

About You

Proven experience in a functional Business Analyst role.
Solid stakeholder management and communication skills, including influencing and negotiation.
Effective time management skills with the ability to prioritise tasks.
Experience with the Atlassian suite - JIRA and Confluence.
Facilitation experience for sprint planning and scrum events.

Why You’ll Love Working Here

Internal Women in Technology Community: Be part of a network that empowers women in tech and supports professional growth.
AWS Training and Membership: Access to training and resources to deepen your AWS expertise and keep up with the latest cloud technologies.
Annual Tech Conferences: Attend industry-leading tech conferences and events to stay at the forefront of innovation.
Hack Days: Participate in our hack days, where creativity and collaboration progress to exciting new ideas and projects.
25 days annual leave (plus flexible working options).
$1050 work-from-home allowance.
Career development programs and learning opportunities.
Onsite concierge services, free meals, and social events.
Generous parental leave and return-to-work benefits. Primary carers: 26 weeks paid + 26 weeks unpaid (up to 52 weeks total) and Secondary carers: 2 weeks paid + 6 weeks unpaid + 1 paid day/week for 3 months.

We value flexibility! Candidates are encouraged to discuss flexible working options during the interview stage.

What’s the Green Tick Feeling?

Well, it’s different for everyone, yet unites us all. It’s the feeling you get when you succeed, no matter what success looks like to you. It could be developing your career, it could be working on an industry leading project, or it could be making it to school pick up in time. It's all the little and big things that make you feel like you’re thriving when working at Sportsbet. 

We’re an inclusive employer who welcomes you for who you are, as you are – so, if you require adjustments to the recruitment process, please let us know in your application. We also know flex means different things to different people, so let us know how we can support you to be your best. 



What Happens Next

Once you apply, our Talent Acquisition team will review your CV. If successful, we’ll contact you for an initial phone call to discuss the role and potential next steps. We’re reviewing applications as they come in; don’t wait!

Check out our Life@Sportsbet Instagram, LinkedIn, and careers website for more about our inclusive culture.

Ready for your Green Tick Feeling? Apply now.

Challenger Limited is an ASX-listed investment management firm managing $123.9 billion in assets (as at 30 June 2025). Life with us is fast moving and always exciting. Together we’re driving to deliver our vision to provide our customers with financial security for a better retirement.

We achieve this goal by providing a work environment where people from diverse backgrounds, with a range of skills and experiences can contribute and succeed.

Senior Business Analyst - Strategic Transactions (12‑month MTC)

Location: Sydney (Hybrid) Team: COO, Life Strategic Transactions

Are you ready to use your business analysis and facilitation skills to make complex work simple on a high‑profile, enterprise‑wide programme?

We’re looking for an experienced Senior Business Analyst to join our Corporate Development & Strategic Initiatives team, supporting a high‑profile, business‑critical programme.

We work flexibly from our Sydney CBD Office where you can expect to work 3 days in the office and 2 days from home.

About the role

As a Senior Business Analyst, you’ll be working alongside Project and Programme leads. You’ll partner with stakeholders across quant, actuarial, finance, product, risk, development and technology (internal teams and strategic partners) to gather requirements and define business solutions. You’ll identify issues, risks and benefits of existing and proposed solutions and assess broader business impacts.

You take a proactive, self‑driven approach to problem‑solving and requirements analysis. Responsibilities include (but aren’t limited to):

Collaborating with stakeholders to gather, document and analyse business and technical requirements.

Facilitating workshops and working with key business, risk and technology stakeholders to align on outcomes.

Working with offshore technology partners to support delivery workstreams and business outcomes.

Data analysis: Analyse and interpret complex data sets to identify trends, patterns and insights; conduct gap analysis.

Process mapping: Document and analyse current business processes; identify opportunities for improvement and efficiency.

Clear documentation: Create and maintain comprehensive, easy‑to‑understand documentation, including requirements and process artefacts.

Governance and compliance: Help ensure appropriate controls for material transactions and support reporting obligations.

Reporting: Support board reporting and presentations to internal boards, committees, and regulators as required.

Skills and experience

You’ll have a strong background as a Senior Business Analyst, or demonstrable BA experience with potential to progress, from within a financial services environment. You thrive in dynamic settings, embracing change and ambiguity while keeping stakeholders aligned.

As well as:

Strong experience in requirement gathering and translating business needs into IT‑ready specifications.

Excellent communication, presentation and facilitation skills - you listen, include and build trust. You can present ideas effectively to groups and senior stakeholders.

Hands‑on experience running workshops and bringing people together to clarify requirements and agree solutions.

Adaptable and resilient in a fast‑paced environment, able to navigate ambiguity and shifting priorities with confidence.

Familiarity with BA tools and methodologies.

Project management experience is a plus.

Highly desirable

Experience with reinsurance, annuities or retirement products is desirable but not essential.

Why Challenger?

At Challenger, we’re small enough to be agile, but big enough to accelerate bold ideas. We support your growth and development, offering flexibility and a culture that values your unique contributions.

Our client is currently seeking a Data Analyst to join their Infrastructure Services Division and bring strong technical, digital and data skills to translate complex business requirements into practical, high-quality solutions that meet evolving business needs. 

In this role you will analyse and interpret data, support the development of metadata standards, assist with data migration, and contribute to the design of a Common Data Model for asset management. This role also focuses heavily on conducting data discovery, standardising reporting and analytics to uplift data literacy and enable self-service analytics across the Division.

As the Data Analyst, you will:

Collaborate with internal and external stakeholders to understand data requirements, ensure alignment with organisational goals, and provide insights that support datadriven decision-making and governance priorities.
Deliver data analysis, profiling, and auditing activities to support business requirements, identify data quality issues, and improve the accuracy and reliability of data assets.
Manage the development of a consolidated data inventory by identifying ownership gaps, creating a pain-point heatmap, and providing recommendations to inform prioritisation.
Advise on the development and implementation of metadata standards, master data rules, and integration frameworks to establish robust data foundations for asset management.
Collaboratively design and deliver interactive, visually engaging Power BI reports and dashboards that align with user needs and enable data-driven decision-making.
Ensure the standardisation and automation of reporting processes by leveraging enterprise tools such as Microsoft Power BI and Fabric.
Evaluate and maintain data accuracy, consistency, and quality by performing validation checks, optimising query performance, and contributing to data governance initiatives.
Document and maintain data processes, workflows, and methodologies, ensuring adherence to best practice standards and version control principles.
 
What you’ll bring to the role:

Proven experience in collating, analysing, and integrating data from multiple disparate systems with varying levels of data maturity.
Strong skills in data analysis, profiling, and quality assessment to identify gaps, inconsistencies, and opportunities for improvement in data assets.
Proficiency in SQL for querying and transforming data.
Strong problem-solving and critical-thinking capability, with the ability to navigate ambiguity, identify issues early, and propose practical solutions.
Proficiency in SQL for querying and transforming data, with experience in Python and Microsoft Fabric Notebooks being highly desirable.
Experience with ETL/ELT processes and tools, particularly in environments with low data maturity.
Understanding of data governance and metadata management practices, with the ability to implement foundational standards and processes.
 
HOW TO APPLY:
Please submit your resume for consideration via the appropriate link. A cover letter demonstrating your relevant experience may also be reviewed.

Should you wish to discuss, please contact Jemma Walker at Jemma.Walker@hudson.com quoting reference number: 248092. Your interest will be treated in the strictest of confidence.

About Us

Praemium was founded in 2001 to simplify the complexities of wealth management. Today, we provide a suite of integrated platforms that support investment administration, portfolio reporting, cash management, trading, and custody services, enabling advisers and institutions to manage every aspect of an investor’s wealth efficiently. We currently manage over $67 billion in funds under administration, delivering innovative technology and reliable service to private wealth clients, financial advisers, and institutional investors.

The Role

We are seeking an experienced Senior Investment Analyst to join our Investment Managers & Governance team. This is a senior, high-impact role responsible for helping ensure Praemium’s Investment Menus remain relevant and compliant in an increasingly complex regulatory environment.

Reporting to the Head of Investment Governance, you will play a critical role in driving fund review, oversight, and investment governance across the platform. You will conduct in-depth due diligence on external investment managers across a broad range of asset classes, provide ongoing investment monitoring, and present recommendations to Investment Committees to support informed decision-making. This role is ideally based in Melbourne, with a hybrid working model (approximately 2–3 days per week in the office)

This role is suited to a seasoned investment professional looking to step into a senior governance-focused position with meaningful influence over platform investment outcomes.

Key Responsibilities

Conduct comprehensive investment and organisational due diligence on external fund managers across multiple asset classes, including single-strategy and multi-manager investments
Produce high-quality research, analysis, and written due diligence reports to support investment recommendations for Platform Investment Menus
Present investment analysis, monitoring outcomes, and recommendations to Investment Committees and other senior stakeholders
Undertake ongoing investment monitoring, including periodic manager reviews, performance and returns analysis, and identification of investments requiring further investigation
Prepare and coordinate attribution analysis in liaison with fund managers
Manage and maintain investment manager data, research databases, and analytical tools
Support onboarding of new investment managers and related operational activities

Desired Qualifications, Experience and Competencies

Degree in Finance or a related discipline
CFA qualification or progress toward CFA accreditation is highly regarded
Minimum 7 years’ experience in multi-manager fund research, asset consulting, and/or fund ratings (essential)
Proven experience researching funds across multiple asset classes
Strong understanding of investment markets, platform financial products, and their use by financial advisers and clients
Experience with managed fund structures and Model / SMA operations (desirable)
Familiarity with retail investment and superannuation regulation, including trustee requirements (highly regarded)
Experience presenting investment recommendations and reviews to Investment Committees and managing complex stakeholder expectations
Outstanding written, verbal, and presentation communication skills
Demonstrated ability to exercise sound investment judgement and influence outcomes through well-reasoned recommendations
Advanced capability in Microsoft Excel; experience with Morningstar Direct and FactSet preferred

What We Offer

Permanent full-time opportunity
Flexible hybrid work environment, up to 2 days from home
Annual bonus opportunity
Access to novated leasing, financial wellness programs and learning opportunities
Tailored professional development
Modern office with end-of-trip facilities at 367 Collins Street, Melbourne

How to Apply

Please apply with your CV, emphasising how your experience and career aligns with the key responsibilities this role. Applicants must have full, unrestricted Australian working rights. Police checks apply to successful candidates.

About the role
We are looking for an experienced Test Analyst for a collaborative data team on a hybrid contract basis in Hawthorn, Melbourne. This role supports high-impact data warehouse and BI initiatives, partnering with Data Engineers and Power BI Developers to validate ETL pipelines, dimensional models, and reporting outputs through rigorous testing.

Key responsibilities

Collaborate with business stakeholders, data engineers, and BI developers to understand requirements, source-to-target mappings (STM), and data models for testing scope.
Design, document, and execute test cases across system integration, regression, and UAT phases, with strong emphasis on data validation, gap analysis verification, and traceability via RTM.
Manage defect lifecycles, facilitate UAT workshops, escalate risks/issues, and produce clear test plans, execution reports, and documentation for technical/business audiences.
Validate ETL processes, Power BI data flows, and dimensional models (e.g., Kimball facts/dimensions) against business requirements and STM documents.
Support test data preparation, environment coordination, and ongoing enhancements to testing artefacts as priorities evolve.​
  
Key skills and experience

Strong foundational knowledge of data systems, data modelling (e.g., star schemas, SCDs), and ETL concepts to validate warehouse outputs.
Proven stakeholder management: engaging business users for UAT, negotiating timelines, and managing expectations around data quality defects.
Hands-on test management tooling (e.g., Jira/Xray, Azure DevOps, HP ALM) with expertise in test design, RTM maintenance, and defect reporting.
Excellent documentation skills for test plans, cases, STM traceability, and gap analysis artefacts.
Solid testing experience in data/BI contexts: data validation, ETL verification, and non-functional checks (e.g., refresh reliability).
Clear communication, detail-oriented mindset, and ability to thrive in hybrid team environments

How to Apply

About the role 

Brisbane | Full-time, Permanent | Hybrid Working 

Join QIC as a Senior Trade Operations Analyst and become part of a global investment manager with a reputation for delivering strong returns while making a positive impact for our clients and people. In this fast-paced role, you’ll coordinate trade flows, ensure data integrity across investment systems, and play a key role in trade lifecycle management. You’ll work closely with internal teams and external partners, contributing to best-in-class operational service and supporting QIC’s commitment to responsible investing and continuous improvement. You’ll be joining a team with deep industry experience, strong technical capability, and a culture that values ownership, continuous improvement, and learning. 

Key Responsibilities 

  

Manage trade workflows across key asset classes including, Fixed Income, Foreign Exchange, Exchange Traded Derivatives, Cleared and Bilateral OTC Derivatives and Private Debt. 
Reconcile positions, market values, and cash within internal and external vendor systems. 
Manage trade lifecycle activities for physical and derivative assets. 
Manage ETD / OTC collateral and margin workflows. 
Oversee external middle office, custodian and clearing functions. 
Contribute to new asset workflows and client initiatives. 

About You 

You are a proactive and detail-oriented trade operations professional who takes ownership of your work and enjoys being part of a collaborative, high performing team. You bring: 

Qualifications in Business, Commerce, Finance or similar. 
Experience in trade operations within an investment management or financial services environment.  
Strong asset knowledge and technical understanding of trade lifecycle processes. 
Knowledge of swap processing, clearing operations, and corporate actions. 
Knowledge of settlement practices across multiple asset types. 
Understanding of investment instruments and in-depth knowledge of pricing and valuation methodologies. 
Strong analytical skills, attention to detail, and problem-solving ability. 
Experience using BlackRock Aladdin (highly regarded). 
Advanced Excel skills, with experience using PowerQuery.

What we’re about

Welcome to RPF, where we believe in keeping it Real.

Generous perks including day off for your anniversary, product discounts, volunteering days to help the community, novated leases, a rewards program and parental leave.

About the role

We are seeking to engage a Business Performance Analyst to join our expanding OneDx business unit. This role supports the identification and delivery of operational productivity in our planned maintenance and capital works portfolio through the development and maintenance of high‑quality analytical reports.

Working closely with Operations and Senior Management, the position provides timely, accurate insights to enable informed decision‑making. The role contributes to research and implementation of continuous improvement initiatives and plays a critical part in proactive risk identification and management.

Strong planning, analytical and business acumen are essential, along with a proactive, solutions‑focused approach to meeting deadlines, targets and reporting requirements with minimal supervision.

 

Key Responsibilities include

Supporting the development and ongoing management of the Maintenance and Capital Works Program Delivery Plan, including identification of risks, issues, dependencies and delivery strategies.
Monitoring and reporting on portfolio and program performance, critical activities and contractual metrics against agreed targets.
Establishing and maintaining portfolio governance, risk and contingency frameworks aligned to ISO 31000 and corporate requirements.
Developing and managing enterprise‑wide analytics and reporting frameworks to deliver timely, accurate and actionable insights.
Providing operational, financial and performance analysis to support data‑driven decision‑making across the business.
Ensuring data integrity, reliability and compliance within agreed governance and portfolio tolerances.
Supporting resource, cost, budgeting and forecasting analysis to improve efficiency, productivity and profitability.
Identifying and implementing process, system and reporting improvements to enhance accuracy, timeliness and consistency.
Engaging with internal and external stakeholders to communicate insights, support audits, close actions and align delivery objectives.

About You

The ideal candidate’s profile will highlight strong analytical and commercial capability, underpinned by a solid understanding of electricity distribution operations or similar industries. It will demonstrate the ability to translate complex data into clear, actionable insights, along with intellectual curiosity, adaptability and collaborative leadership to support informed decision‑making and continuous improvement across the business.

Demonstrated experience delivering advanced analytics and reporting to support operational, commercial and strategic decision‑making in a complex business environment.
Proven experience within electricity distribution or a similar infrastructure‑based industry, with maintenance and construction activities.
Experience translating complex business requirements and data into actionable insights, recommendations and clear stakeholder communications.
Proven experience working with financial analysis, budgeting, forecasting and performance management to drive productivity and risk‑informed outcomes.
Experience engaging with and influencing senior stakeholders, managing competing priorities and contributing to continuous improvement initiatives.

 

We are a champion of equal opportunity employment and have committed to targets for gender equity and first nations representation in our workforce. We want you to come as you are by promoting an inclusive culture, both within our organisation and throughout the communities we interact with.

About SEEK

At SEEK, we serve a noble purpose: to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and to help organisations succeed.

Why join us?

Be part of a multi-national tech company with strong core values to help us solve complex challenges for our customers while building a flexible, exciting career – one that could take you anywhere.

We’re looking for people who thrive in dynamic teams and enjoy tackling regular new challenges in a large-scale, modern, and agile environment. Job Description

About the role

The Product Manager – Monetisation & Insights (add-ons) creates new add-on products that support hirers across APAC markets. Add-ons are a critical revenue stream that complement job ad campaigns and drive SEEK's long-term monetisation strategy. You will:

Build deep customer segmentation knowledge (by contract value, industry, role mix) to identify hiring needs and product opportunities
Research marketplace add-on strategies and monetised value propositions to inform product decisions
Partner with cross-functional teams to design add-ons that maximize customer value and integrate with ad and non-ad products
Establish feedback loops with customers and sales teams to inform roadmap prioritization

This role requires a marketplace perspective that balances hirer needs with candidate experience. You'll collaborate closely with Commercial, Product Marketing, Strategy, and Sales teams across APAC.

The team

Reporting to the Principal PM – Ad Products and Add-ons, the Product Manager is part of a passionate team working collaboratively with other Product teams, UX, AI Platform Services, Analytics, Engineering, and key stakeholders across Strategy, Commercial Excellence, and Sales to identify and execute on new initiatives. You will manage and drive the product design deliverables (e.g. UX designs, research, user testing) and work within a development team to ensure smooth delivery.

Responsibilities

Own a problem space at the core of transforming and innovating our add-on capabilities to better meet customer needs.
Be central to the transformation of our business model, and be a leader in challenging our status quo.
Actively manage and engage stakeholders across the business to ensure strategic objectives are being met.
Be a relentless customer advocate with a focus on delivering great user experiences that solve real customer problems.
Ideate and validate opportunities and problems, inclusive of strategic fit and financial assessment.
Develop execution plans, and deliver enhancements and new functionality for our Contracted Hirers (working in concert with other relevant teams who also build non-job ad value).
Own key metrics / outcomes related to Contracted Hirers and Insights.
Stay abreast of technology, industry and competitor trends.
Qualifications

Skills and experience

Strategic problem-solver, comfortable working in a space with significant ambiguity.
Structured decision-maker able to consider complex, nuanced tradeoffs, make decisive judgments, and bring others along with you.
Strong customer focus, with a passion for identifying and solving customer needs.
Commercial acumen, able to consider business constraints and objectives.
Strong analytical skills, comfortable with data and working with data scientists to improve the performance of our products.
Ability to lead cross-functional teams to deliver business outcomes.
Able to influence and persuade at all levels of the organisation and build and maintain strong stakeholder relationships.
Considerable experience in product development with solid understanding of agile software development, across customer discovery and delivery.
Experience working with AI and AI teams is an advantage.
Well-developed communication, presentation and interpersonal skills.
Belief in and passion for SEEK’s Purpose.
Additional Information

Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role
Annual Performance Bonus Plan
The opportunity to work from anywhere for up to 4 weeks per financial year
Frequent events including sports days, year-end party, hackathon, and trivia
Casual dress every day
